== Current Situation == Student politics in Bangladesh is reactive, confrontational, and violent. [[Student organization]]s act as armaments of the political parties they are part of.<ref>{{cite web | last = Kalam | first = Hadi | title = Political Violence Of Chatra League: A Chronology | url = http://perspectivebd.com/2014/02/political-violence-of-chatra-league-a-chronology/ | accessdate = 6 May 2015}}</ref> So every now and then there are affrays and commotions. <ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | title = Frequent violence plagues campus atmosphere | url = http://newsfrombangladesh.net/view.php?hidRecord=303629 | accessdate = 6 May 2015}}</ref> Over the years, political clashes and factional feuds in [[university|universities]] killed many, seriously interfering with academics.<ref>{{cite web | last = Rangpur Correspondent | first = bdnews24.com | title = Rangpur Medical College shut down indefinitely after BCL clash leaves 10 injured | url = http://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2015/04/15/rangpur-medical-college-shut-down-indefinitely-after-bcl-clash-leaves-10-injured | accessdate = 6 May 2015}}</ref> To relieve tensions, universities often must resort to lengthy closures, resulting in truncated and overcrowded classes.
The student wings of ruling parties run [[campus|campuses]] and [[residence hall]]s through [[crime]] and violence. They control access to amenities in residence halls, favoring fellow [[party member]]s and loyal pupils; eat for free from nearby [[restaurant]]s, and help themselves to products from shops nearby; practice [[extortion]]; and take money from [[freshman|freshmen]]. Further, they put pressure on [[teacher]]s for payment in exchange for supporting to school administration their hiring and [[tenure|retention]].<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = Research Directorate, Immigration and Refugee Board, Canada | last2 = | first2 = | last3 = | first3 = | last4 = | first4 = | title = Political Parties and Political Violence | website = Refworld | publisher = Research Directorate, Immigration and Refugee Board, Canada | date = May 1, 1994 | url = http://www.refworld.org/docid/3ae6a8670.html | access-date = April 28, 2015 }}</ref> <ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | last2 = | first2 = | last3 = | first3 = | last4 = | first4 = | title = Academic activities resume in IU | newspaper = Daily Prothom Alo | date = June 27, 2015 | url = http://en.prothom-alo.com/bangladesh/news/70585/Academic-activities-resume-in-IU | access-date = June 27, 2015 }}</ref>
